history.content: 4 techs sounds like an awful lot to me. I would advise against it.

Hey, everyone!


I'm planning to take a challenging workload next semester, but one that leaves me enough time to invest time into research, a club, and any side projects that take my fancy.

As of now, I've enrolled into Math 110 and EE126, and am #117 on the waitlist for CS 168. I'm thinking of trying to enrol into CS186 in Phase 2 to complete my class list for next semester - do you think this workload matches my goals (in terms of challenging but enough time to work on above interests)? 

For context, I've taken every lower-div except EE16A, and I've taken/taking CS170, CS188 and CS189 so far, and I'm a LSCS major.
history.subject: Suggestions/Comments on proposed workload
